\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1 Dots on the computer follows the same rules as Dots on a regular sheet of paper.
\par 
\par Try playing a 2 player local game first, enter a height and a width, press Start!
\par Then move your mouse between 2 dots, you will notice a line forms, click and for your turn you will create that line.  If 4 lines connect to make a box, you get to go again.  At the end of the game whoever has more boxes wins.
\par 
\par To play on the Internet, read below how to connect and host.  Then you can chat through the Multiplayer Chat Window.  The rest of the game goes as normal except now you can only make a line when it is your turn, when it isn\rquote t your turn you will get
 a Hand with the message NO! on it, this means it is the other players turn.
\par 
