\par }{\f1 Connect \endash  This allows you to connect to another player over the internet who is currently hosting a game.  Type in their IP address in the slot and choose a nickname for yourself, then press connect.
\par 
\par Host \endash  This allows you to host an online game for others to connect to, tell people your IP address and choose a level size, who goes first, a nickname, then press Listen.  People can only connect to you while you are \'93Listening\'94, pressing th
e \'93Listening\'94 button will cause you to stop listening.
\par 
\par Go to Chat Server \endash  Connect to an internet chat server to find many people who are willing to host games for you to connect to.  You can also host games and have other people connect to them.  Go to the chat server and talk to people there, you may
 also get more help from them!
\par 
\par Show Multiplayer Chat Window \endash  If you are playing an online game in order to chat with your opponent, use this window, you can send messages to them that way.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Online Button
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1 This button appears while you are in an online game
\par 
\par New Game \endash  Option is only available to the host, this allows you to create a new game, useful after one game ends and you want to start anther one.
\par 
\par Synchronize Game \endash  Makes sure that the games look exactly the same, this is incase you feel something fishy happened with the connection and the games do wrong things (ie a box comes out of nowhere)
 press this and it will go back to whatever the hosts game looks like.  In the game there is a built in autosync feature, this tries to resynchronize the games with out you realizing there is a problem.  This happens rarely but it does help.
\par 
\par Disconnect \endash  End your online game
